THE JOB



Reporting to the Administration & Board Manager (ABM), the Assistant Administration & Board Manager will be responsible for the following duties:

To assist in providing secretariat and logistic supports for the Board and Committees meetings and activities including drafting, translating and editing of minutes, papers and reports etc.;
To assistance in providing administrative support in executing the company secretary functions in compliance with the statutory requirements of the Companies Ordinance and the HKSIL Articles of Association;
To assist in reviewing and drafting of internal administration procedures and guidelines;
To assist in the supervision of the Administrative Assistants and handle any other administrative duties as directed by the ABM; and
To perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.


THE REQUIREMENTS

A recognised university degree in languages (English preferred), public administration or equivalent;
A minimum of 4 years' relevant working experience. Relevant experience in the HKSAR Government or public sector organisations will be a definite asset;
Excellent command of both spoken and written English and Chinese. Ability to speak Putonghua would be an added advantage;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Able to work under pressure; and
High level of computer literacy.



